    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-01-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Japanese Chargé</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Hioki</hi>: I send you informally a copy of a
                        letter<note n="a" xml:id="d134fna">Not printed.</note> from the Secretary of
                    Agriculture communicating one to him from Mr. B. F. Tillinghast, of Davenport,
                    Iowa, stating that the Davenport Democrat would feel it a duty to invite
                    subscriptions and apply them in such manner as your legation might authorize to
                    relieve the suffering caused by famine in the northeastern provinces of
                    Japan.</p>
                <p>The department has no advices on the subject of the alleged famine, and I
                    therefore beg to inquire whether the situation is, in fact, so serious that
                    outside contributions would be acceptable.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
